Now I understand the change. The key insight is:

Before this change, when the planner produced no task files but the harness seed kicked in and produced fallback (harness-seeded) tasks, the manifest would report `planning_failed = False`. This meant the evidence-backed planning system was silently treating a no-task planning session as successful, just because there were *some* tasks (even if they were all harness fallback seeds).

The fix: `planning_failed` is now `True` when all tasks are harness-seeded — not just when there are zero tasks. And the `harness_seeded` computation was moved up so it could be used in the `planning_failed` condition.

This connects to the Day 114 earlier sessions where the system was detecting "no-edit streaks" and "analysis paralysis" — this is another piece of the same puzzle: making sure the system correctly recognizes when the planner failed so it can take corrective action.

